            {
              "id": 1052152976,
              "helpfulVotes": 1,
              "rating": 5,
              "title": "Expectations Met, But Underwhelmed",
              "text": "This 4S is probably not as nice as many, but it’s still the gold standard in Cairo. We had a premium Nile view king for four nights and it was fine. Only complaint is a lack of horizontal space in the room—no place to put packing cubes, etc. Great location. Nice breakfast. Ate at the Italian resto on Valentines Day. There was a set menu which was a bit too much. Also ate at “8” the Asian-themed resto. Food was good, but service seemed a bit confused. Lobby bar is very nice, as is the bar above the pool area. Beware though . . . Cocktails and imported wine are extremely expensive. All-in-all a pleasant stay, if a bit underwhelming.",
              "status": "PUBLISHED",
              "tripInfo": {
                "stayDate": "2026-02-28",
                "tripType": "COUPLES"
              },
              "location": {
                "name": "Four Seasons Hotel Cairo at Nile Plaza",
                "locationId": 308077,
                "parentGeoId": 294201,
                "absoluteUrl": "https://www.tripadvisor.com/Hotel_Review-g294201-d308077-Reviews-Four_Seasons_Hotel_Cairo_at_Nile_Plaza-Cairo_Cairo_Governorate.html"
              },
              "locationId": 308077,
              "publishedDate": "2026-03-06",
              "ownerResponseId": 1053057920,
              "ownerResponse": {
                "id": 1053057920,
                "text": "Dear Giddypam, \n\nThank you for taking the time to share such a thoughtful and detailed review of your recent stay with us. While I’m glad to know that you enjoyed our central location, Nile views, breakfast offering, and the atmosphere of our lounges, I’m truly sorry to learn that certain elements of your visit fell short of the seamless experience we strive to deliver.\n\nYour comments regarding the layout and available space in your guest room are very helpful, and I appreciate you bringing this to our attention. We continuously review our accommodations to ensure they are as comfortable and functional as possible, and your feedback will certainly be considered in our ongoing improvements.\n\nI am also grateful for your notes on the dining experiences, from the set Valentine’s Day menu to the service at 8 Restaurant. While I’m pleased to hear you enjoyed the cuisine, I regret that the service felt anything less than intuitive. This is not reflective of the standard we aim to provide, and I will be reviewing your impressions with our restaurant teams to ensure greater consistency and clarity.\n\nRegarding pricing of imported beverages, I understand how this may have impacted your impression. We do our best to balance quality, availability, and guest experience, and your perspective is invaluable as we assess these offerings.\n\nThank you once again for your honest insight. I’m pleased that your stay was pleasant overall, but I sincerely hope we have the opportunity to welcome you back and deliver a visit that feels truly exceptional in every way.\n\nKind regards,\nYves Giacometti\nRegional Vice President and General Manager\nFour Seasons Hotel Cairo at Nile Plaza",
                "publishedDate": "2026-03-15",
                "userId": "899A6C25D9A89BF78DCEB776F45CC1B3",
